Ecology. Endogeic species occurring in deciduous and coniferous forests as well as on arable and grassland sites, prefers high soil organic matter content (> 4 %) (
Zuck 1951
;
Jänsch et al. 2013
). Sometimes dominant in wet meadows (
Graff 1954
).

